post_text:
INTRODUCING THE 2020-21 LaMonte FFA Officer Team:

President- Aaron Anderson
Vice President- Keeley Elwell
Secretary- Karen Cisneros
Treasurer- Jacob Dixon
Reporter- Aiden Knoerschild
Sentinel- Logan Mahin

They recently attended the 2020 Area 8 Leadership Conference in Otterville.

They attended three different workshops:
How to be a quality leader
- Including learning not everyone can be a leader at once and you must listen to everyone. Also that communication is key.

Find your rhythm- They learned that different skills can work good together.

Ag. Ed on the move - They learned about the opportunities Ag. Ed in the classroom has. Including teaching K-6th about the importance of Agriculture.
#vikingstrong #teamlamonte

post_text:
The La Monte math team went to Kaysinger math contest at SFCC on Tuesday, March 10th. We competed against 9 schools and were 7th. We won 7 medals and 2 ribbons. #teamlamonte

Brendan Green placed 4th (ribbon) in Algebra 10, 3rd (medal) in Word Problems 10, 5th (ribbon) in Analytical Geometry & Graphing, and 6th in Hodgepodge 10.

Liam Kincaid placed 8th in Word Problems 12.

Rebaeka Natale placed 9th in Algebra 12, 6th in Word Problems 12, 10th in Trigonometry, and 7th in Hodgepodge 12.

Ariana Olmedo placed 6th in Algebra 10, 8th in Word Problems 10, and 8th in Hodgepodge 10.

Emma Schouten placed 10th in Word Problems 11, and 6th in Geometry 11.

The Medley Team formed of Gregorio Quezada, Emma Schouten, and Liam Kincaid placed 2nd (of 7).

The Sophomore Team formed of Brendan, Ariana, and Saraih Navarro placed 1st (of 9).

At last night's School Board meeting the Board voted to adopted a four day school week calendar beginning next year.

CTC, JROTC, and the early childhood special education preschool (Sedalia) will continue as currently scheduled and still include transportation.

We are working to create a child care program for pre-K-5th grades. We will announce other programs and changes as they are developed.
